Author-Name:   Burnkrant, Robert E
Author-Name:  Unnava, H Rao
Title: 
 Effects of Self-Referencing on Persuasion.

Journal: Journal of Consumer Research
Pages: 17-26
Issue: 1
Volume: 22
Year: 1995
Month:  June 
Abstract:

 Two experiments manipulate self-referencing by varying copy writing
 strategy. It is found that increasing self-referencing increases message
 elaboration and can increase persuasion when message arguments are strong.
 However, when self-referencing is increased in the presence of other
 variables that also enhance elaboration, the favorable effect of
 self-referencing on persuasion is moderated or reversed. A two-factor
 explanation is employed to generate predictions and account for results.


