Author-Name:   Muthukrishnan, A V
Title: 
 Decision Ambiguity and Incumbent Brand Advantage.

Journal: Journal of Consumer Research
Pages: 98-109
Issue: 1
Volume: 22
Year: 1995
Month:  June 
Abstract:

 This article examines the role of decision ambiguity in judgments that
 consumers make about an incumbent (the brand a consumer currently uses)
 versus an attack brand (a new, superior competitor). It is hypothesized
 that decision ambiguity creates an advantage for the incumbent. A
 conceptualization of decision ambiguity is offered. In three experiments,
 factors that can cause decision ambiguity are manipulated and their
 effects on preference for the incumbent are investigated. The results
 underscore the role of decision ambiguity in incumbent brand advantage. In
 two other experiments, boundary conditions are examined.


